entity.extra:
{
  "displayName": "App Autoscaler",
  "documentationUrl": "https://docs.cfexample.com/pivotalcf/2-5/appsman-services/autoscaler/using-autoscaler.html",

}

entity.label: p-redis
entity.description: Redis service to provide pre-provisioned instances configured as a datastore, running on a shared VM.
entity.extra:
{
  "displayName": "Redis",
  "documentationUrl": "http://docs.cfexample.com/redis/index.html",
  "imageUrl": "data:image/png;base64,",
  "longDescription": "The shared VM service allows app developers to provision Redis instances on a shared VM. The shared-vm service is intended for development only. The shared VM service allows the operator to configure instance usage quotas, log forwarding, instance-level metrics and backups.",
  "providerDisplayName": "Pivotal",
  "supportUrl": "http://support.cfexample.com"
}

entity.label: p.redis
entity.description: Redis service to provide on-demand dedicated instances configured as a cache.
entity.extra:
{
  "displayName": "Redis On-Demand",
  "imageUrl": "data:image/png;base64,",
  "longDescription": "For the on-demand service, the operator can configure up to three service plans for dynamically provisioned instances with different memory and disk sizes. App Developers can provision instances as needed until the instance quota is met. Operators and App Developers can set certain Redis configurations to tailor an instance to an application's needs. This service offers quotas to manage instance use, log-forwarding and plan-level metrics.",
  "providerDisplayName": "Pivotal",
  "shareable": false
}
